abstract: John Risher has been recording statistics as a volunteer at Virginia’s home football games since 1963, and he shows no signs of stopping anytime soon.
snippet: John Risher has been recording statistics as a volunteer at Virginia’s home football games since 1963, and he shows no signs of stopping anytime soon.
lead_paragraph: CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. — John Risher drove north on Route 29, a briefcase resting in the car’s back seat.

abstract: Often the motivation for giving is personal experience.
snippet: Often the motivation for giving is personal experience.
lead_paragraph: After years rising through the ranks in the insurance industry, Jay S. Fishman reached the pinnacle of his professional career when he became the chief executive of Travelers in 2004. But nothing prepared him for the diagnosis he received in 2014 of amyotrophic lateral sclerosis, or Lou Gehrig’s disease, the irreversible neurodegenerative disease that attacks the nerve cells in the brain and spinal cord.

abstract: The former “S.N.L.” star Jason Sudeikis plays the stage version of John Keating, the teacher made famous by Robin Williams.

lead_paragraph: Still soaking in the happy haze that surrounds you after you’ve welcomed a new life into the world, Jason Sudeikis was contemplating his expanding obligations as an adult.

abstract: People call them old-man cars — but what’s so bad about growing up?
snippet: People call them old-man cars — but what’s so bad about growing up?
lead_paragraph: The moment my father pulled into the driveway with his new Buick LeSabre Limited was one of his proudest. He parked the car in the center of our circular driveway, right by the front door, and beckoned my mother and me to come have a look. The LeSabre was a beautiful car, the color of Champagne. It had a tufted velour interior, soft vinyl doors and a faux-walnut dashboard that lit up warm as a hearth.

abstract: Born and raised in South Africa, Mr. Noah talks about growing up poor there, and his mother’s beat-up, tangerine Volkswagen Beetle.
snippet: Born and raised in South Africa, Mr. Noah talks about growing up poor there, and his mother’s beat-up, tangerine Volkswagen Beetle.
lead_paragraph: When I was 5 years old, we moved to Eden Park, a neighborhood adjacent to several black townships on the outskirts of Johannesburg — half-colored and half-black, my mother figured, like us. It was me and her, alone. There was this sense of the two of us embarking on a grand adventure. We weren’t just mother and son. We were a team.

headline_main: Trevor Noah: The First Time I Drove a Car. (I Was 6.)

abstract: Baseball scouts used to scrutinize Maury Lerner’s every move. Then F.B.I. agents were the ones watching.
snippet: Baseball scouts used to scrutinize Maury Lerner’s every move. Then F.B.I. agents were the ones watching.
lead_paragraph: The Buick sedan crawled the Providence streets. The April sky was baby blue, the air pleasant and cool. Perfect baseball weather. The man hunched in the back seat once lived for days like this.

headline_main: The Big League Prospect Who Became a Mob Hit Man

abstract: The president, widening his attack on Mr. Trump, excoriated Representative Joe Heck of Nevada and others for failing to reject the candidate earlier.
snippet: The president, widening his attack on Mr. Trump, excoriated Representative Joe Heck of Nevada and others for failing to reject the candidate earlier.
lead_paragraph: NORTH LAS VEGAS, Nev. — President Obama on Sunday savaged Representative Joe Heck, Republican of Nevada, for failing to reject Donald J. Trump earlier in the presidential race, seeking to tarnish Mr. Heck and other Republican candidates across the country by association with a standard-bearer he called indecent and unfit for the presidency.

headline_main: For Republicans Abandoning Donald Trump, Obama Has a Message: ‘Too Late’
headline_print_headline: For Republicans Abandoning Trump, Obama Has a Message: ‘Too Late’

abstract: Organizations supporting Mrs. Clinton have raised nearly $200 million, defying expectations that conservatives and corporations would dominate spending.
snippet: Organizations supporting Mrs. Clinton have raised nearly $200 million, defying expectations that conservatives and corporations would dominate spending.
lead_paragraph: Six years after a Supreme Court decision opened vast new channels for money to flow into national elections, Democrats have built the largest and best-coordinated apparatus of outside groups operating in the 2016 presidential campaign, defying expectations that conservative and corporate wealth would dominate the race.

abstract: The battle to succeed Senator Harry Reid of Nevada, who is retiring, is one of a handful of contests that could determine control of Congress.
snippet: The battle to succeed Senator Harry Reid of Nevada, who is retiring, is one of a handful of contests that could determine control of Congress.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — For all the millions of dollars spent on this election, the outcome may come down to people like Megan Blas.
